Contact Us

At a minimum, to qualify for our base tier, we look for startups that are:

  • Early-stage: Less than 7 years old and Series A or earlier
  • Building a scalable product: Focused on a single software-based product or service (note: development shops and agencies are not eligible)
  • New participants: Not previously accepted into the MongoDB for Startups program
  • Established online: Have an active company website and LinkedIn profile

We work closely with VCs, accelerators, and incubators. Please ask your VC or accelerator partner to refer you. If your VC or accelerator partner is not part of the MongoDB for Startups program, please ask them to apply.

If you are not involved with a VC, accelerator, or incubator, please apply above on this page.

Absolutely. You do not have to be new to MongoDB to be eligible for our program. We accept both new and existing MongoDB Atlas users.

If you haven't heard back from us after five business days please contact us.

Once you are accepted into the program, you will receive a unique promo code in your welcome email.

To activate your promo code, go to account.mongodb.com and follow these simple steps for the organization you wish to apply the code to:

  1. Log in or create an account
  2. Navigate to Billing
  3. Click the Apply Code button
  4. Enter your Activation Code
  5. Click Submit

Questions about activation? Get step-by-step activation instructions.

Questions about getting started? Discover our MongoDB Atlas guides.

Please note you must be an Organization Owner or Organization Billing Admin to activate your subscription. To change your organization role, contact your organizations IT administrator.

Startups have 12 months to activate their promo code.

Once activated, startups have 12 months to use your Atlas credits.

You can check your current credit balance anytime by logging in to account.mongodb.com

  • Go to Billing in the top navigation bar.
  • Scroll down to Available Credits to view your balance.

To view the expiration date of your credits, please follow the instructions below:

  1. Visit account.mongodb.com
  2. Log in to your existing account
  3. Navigate to the top navigation bar and click Billing
  4. Scroll to the bottom to the Available Credits section
  5. Under the Active Dates column, there will be gray text that states (EXPIRES MM/DD/YY)

What if my credits are expiring or have expired? If you are not able to exhaust your credits in 12 months, you can request an extension (considered on a case-by-case basis). If possible, please contact us when you have three months remaining.

If you havent used all your credits within 12 months, you can request an extension. We review extensions on a case-by-case basis. Just note that promo codes can only be applied to future charges, not past usage.

If you are interested in advice on data best practices and solutions to operational issues, we recommend signing up for the Developer Support plan.

The Developer Support team provides 24/7 support, in-app chat, and support portal access. The first 30 days are free, and you can use your startup Atlas credits to pay beyond that period (starting at $49 per month).

MongoDB also offers a professional services team of experts to accelerate your startups success. As part of this program, you get exclusive access to a one-on-one session with an expert to learn best practices and receive guidance on your startup needs.
